        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 4:36PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 436 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Bosque Del Apache Refuge, or 15 miles south of
Socorro, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bosque Del Apache Refuge and San Antonio.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 380 between Mile Markers 1 and 6.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 127 and 140.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
